result.execSummary:
The defendant James Jay Kwapil was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. James Jay Kwapil is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • James Jay Kwapil was found guilty of Possess Firearm-Contrary to Injunction, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(2)(e).
  • James Jay Kwapil was found guilty of Negligent Handling of a Weapon, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Paid in full - bond previously posted has been applied.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. Defendant is prohibited from being in possession of any firearm whatsoever.

DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed. The court orders forfeiture and destruction of the 9 mm Taurus, 22 caliber Marlin, 22 caliber Taurus, 45 High Point pistol and the 380 Smith & Wesson Body Guard.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

Bond not applied to restitution in the amount of $250 has been applied. Remaining costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

Case called @ 1:57 p.m. Defendant James Jay Kwapil in court with attorney Nathaniel J. Wojan.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Victim appears telephonically. Ct 4 -  6 mos WCJ- Huber, GT, 3 days CFTS -  I/S -  1 year probation concurrent w/ Ct 1 - Same conditions as Ct 1. Bond previously posted to be applied. Appeal rights given.
